# Particle spawning and update

## Spawn

Every 3 ticks, it emits a particle from a random node, up to a max of 40 particles.

```javascript
function spawnParticle() {
  if (particles.length >= config.particleMax) return;

  const node = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
  const angle = Math.random() * TAU;
  const speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * 0.7;

  particles.push({
    x: node.x,
    y: node.y,
    vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
    vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
    age: 0,
    maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
    size: 0.8 + Math.random() * 1.2
  });
}
```

## Update

```javascript
function updateParticles() {
  for (let i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    const p = particles[i];
    p.x += p.vx;
    p.y += p.vy;
    p.vx *= 0.995;
    p.vy *= 0.995;
    p.age++;

    if (p.age > p.maxAge) {
      particles.splice(i, 1);
    }
  }
}
```

Particles just drift and slowly slow down.

Note: `particleFade` exists in config but is not actually used in the code shown. It was probably intended for rendering alpha fade elsewhere.

