# Camera easing

The camera smoothly moves toward a target camera.

```javascript
function updateCamera() {
  camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * config.cameraEase;
  camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * config.cameraEase;
  camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.cameraEase;
}
```

Currently, both camera and target start at the same values and nothing in this snippet changes the target, so camera easing does nothing unless other code modifies `cameraTarget`.

